article.description: Cory Hightower had 21 points and six rebounds as Presbyterian romped past Toccoa Falls College of the NCCAA 87-59 on Saturday.
article.headline: Hightower lifts Presbyterian past Toccoa Falls 87-59
article.linkText: Hightower lifts Presbyterian past Toccoa Falls 87-59
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Cory Hightower had 21 points and six rebounds as Presbyterian romped past Toccoa Falls College of the NCCAA 87-59 on Saturday. Chris Martin had 13 points, seven rebounds, six assists and six steals for Presbyterian (2-6), which ended its five-game losing streak. Ben Drake added 12 points and 12 rebounds. Sean Jenkins had 11 points for the hosts. Jayden Young led Toccoa Falls with 11 points and five boards. Presbyterian plays South Carolina State on the road next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
